name: open-iscsi

variants.name: build_system
variants.description: Build systems supported by the package

description:
The Open-iSCSI project is a high-performance, transport independent,
multi-platform implementation of RFC3720 iSCSI.

dependencies.name: gmake
dependencies.description:
GNU Make is a tool which controls the generation of executables and
other non-source files of a program from the program's source files.

dependencies.name: kmod
dependencies.description:
kmod is a set of tools to handle common tasks with Linux kernel modules
like insert, remove, list, check properties, resolve dependencies and
aliases.

dependencies.name: libtool
dependencies.description: libtool -- library building part of autotools.

dependencies.name: open-isns
dependencies.description:
This is the iSNS server, supporting persistent storage of registrations
in a file based database.

dependencies.name: util-linux
dependencies.description: Util-linux is a suite of essential utilities for any Linux system.

dependencies.name: uuid
dependencies.description:
OSSP uuid is a ISO-C:1999 application programming interface (API) and
corresponding command line interface (CLI) for the generation of DCE
1.1, ISO/IEC 11578:1996 and RFC 4122 compliant Universally Unique
Identifier (UUID).
